#Text=Q :
#Text=Why do you want to represent this particular ward on council ?
#Text=A :
#Text=This is not only a Ward , but it is my home .
#Text=I would be honoured to represent my home and ensure it is looked after to the fullest of my abilities .
#Text=Q :
#Text=How are you currently involved in the community ?
#Text=A :
#Text=Currently I am a volunteer for Community Centre 55 , helping with whatever they need and in their Christmas hamper efforts for many years .
#Text=I have worked with the Lions Club on occasion helping in their Easter Parade work .
#Text=I also have helped for many years in trash cleanup of the area , and have been a leader for Girl Guides of Canada for a local unit for over 10 years .
#Text=Q :
#Text=Which council decision ( since the 2003 election ) do you feel the city/your ward should be most proud of , and which was least desirable ?
#Text=A :
#Text=I was very happy when have bid for Olympics and the World 's Fair .
#Text=I have been to other countries and attended such functions .
#Text=Toronto needs something like this to help the city financially and promote what a wonderful place Toronto is .
#Text=I hope in the future we are awarded such an honour .
#Text=Least Desirable - Having the current city council administer themselves an 8 % wage increase has to be the worst decision they have made to date .
#Text=Their wages and increase should be decided by a non-patrician group with council kept out of the process .
#Text=Q :
#Text=If you were elected as a " rookie " councillor , What would you bring to the table beyond the incumbent ?
#Text=A :
#Text=I hope that I may bring a regular citizens outlook to city council .
#Text=We need a balanced budget , after all everyone else in the general public has to work with the money they have .
#Text=Lastly , we have to realize that we are paid by the people , we work for the people and we should all be accountable to the people on a daily basis .
#Text=Q :
#Text=What does Toronto mean to you ?
#Text=A :
#Text=Toronto is my home .
#Text=It a city full of diversity , and different cultures .
#Text=I have traveled the world and discovered that all that I have purchased is already available to me in Toronto .
#Text=I love the mix of cultures , and the many different restaurants I have frequented .
#Text=I have friends from all over the world .
#Text=I was lucky enough to have a visiting princess meet me in 1979 ; she wanted to meet the most diversified high school in Toronto , and that was my own .
#Text=As a student council member I was formally introduced !
#Text=Then later in 1990 I was present when Princess Diana came through my hospital .
#Text=Where else in the world could you meet a two princesses but in Toronto !
